sometimes simply referred to as a . Since silk kimono are delicate and difficult to clean, the  helps to keep the outer kimono clean by preventing contact with the wearer's skin (paralleling the European petticoat). Only the collar edge of the  shows from beneath the outer kimono. Many  have removable collars, to allow them to be changed to match the outer garment, and to be easily washed without washing the entire garment. They are often as beautifully ornate and patterned as the outer kimono. Since men's kimono are usually fairly subdued in pattern and colour, the  allows for discreetly wearing very striking designs and colours.}}
